    "body": "\r\n# Problem\r\n\r\nNo way to force a lsp client to attach to current buffer (or if there is, please let me know).\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/2708 proposed introducing a \"shebang\" flag to force lsp configs for some special cases, but ultimately, if we can't figure out the correct configs *automatically*, the general solution is to allow users to easily say what to apply (interactively).\r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\n- `:LspStart! foo` should force the \"foo\" config for the current buffer.\r\n    - This may also imply \"single file mode\", I'm not sure. Especially if a \"root\" couldn't be found.",
